00:02:15,135 --> 00:02:17,137
we're bringing back categories.


56
00:02:17,171 --> 00:02:18,639
[Lauren]
There are six categories


57
00:02:18,672 --> 00:02:19,973
for the Apple Design Awards
this year.


58
00:02:20,007 --> 00:02:22,910
-They're inclusivity.
-[Linda] Delight and fun.


59
00:02:22,943 --> 00:02:25,212
-[Doug] Interaction.
-[Allan] Social impact.


60
00:02:25,245 --> 00:02:28,582
-[Mark] Visuals and graphics.
-[Mike] And innovation.


61
00:02:28,615 --> 00:02:31,852
The thing that I love
about what we're doing this year


62
00:02:31,885 --> 00:02:34,188
is that we're able
to really zero in


63
00:02:34,221 --> 00:02:35,923
on some particular qualities


64
00:02:35.956 --> 00:02:38.926 line:-2
that are really important
and to talk about them directly.


65
00:02:38.959 --> 00:02:43.163 line:-1
♪ ♪


66
00:02:43,197 --> 00:02:46,433
[Teo] Apps and games
are hugely powerful


67
00:02:46,466 --> 00:02:49,436
because they can create
environments where, you know,


68
00:02:49,469 --> 00:02:50,804
all are welcome.


69
00:02:50,838 --> 00:02:52,406
♪ ♪


70
00:02:52,439 --> 00:02:55,876
[Linda]
Design is inherently about


71
00:02:55,909 --> 00:02:59,213
understanding and catering
towards people,


72
00:02:59,246 --> 00:03:03,116
so this idea of inclusivity,
it's not anything new,


73
00:03:03,150 --> 00:03:05,619
but it is just making sure
that the goal


74
00:03:05,652 --> 00:03:08,589
is always
to support more people,


75
00:03:08,622 --> 00:03:10,224
to enable more people.


76
00:03:10,257 --> 00:03:12,693
[Aurelio] Well, obviously
ethnicity and age and gender


77
00:03:12,726 --> 00:03:15,195
are some of the big ones,
but all the time,


78
00:03:15,229 --> 00:03:16,563
we're finding more things


79
00:03:16,597 --> 00:03:18,932
that are personally important
to people.


80
00:03:18,966 --> 00:03:20,767
Being inclusive
and being diverse


81
00:03:20,801 --> 00:03:23,036
is being accepting
of those categories


82
00:03:23,070 --> 00:03:24,471
and making sure
that they're represented


83
00:03:24,505 --> 00:03:26,507
in a way that's equitable
to the user.


84
00:03:26,540 --> 00:03:29,710
[Lauren] Apps and games
that excel at inclusivity


85
00:03:29,743 --> 00:03:33,213
include as many people
as possible in the experience.


86
00:03:33,247 --> 00:03:35,015
This can be done
through localization


87
00:03:35,048 --> 00:03:36,550
with a ton of languages.


88
00:03:36,583 --> 00:03:38,619
It can be done
by supporting a wide variety


89
00:03:38,652 --> 00:03:42,289
of accessibility features
like voiceover and dynamic type.


90
00:03:42,322 --> 00:03:45,526
It can be something as simple
as turning on reduced motion


91
00:03:45,559 --> 00:03:48,395
in a game so people
with motion sensitivities


92
00:03:48,428 --> 00:03:51,598
can still have fun
and experience the game fully.


93
00:03:51,632 --> 00:03:54,968
♪ ♪


94
00:03:55,002 --> 00:03:58,138
The winning app
in the Inclusivity category


95
00:03:58,172 --> 00:03:59,973
is Voice Dream Reader.


96
00:04:00,007 --> 00:04:03,911
Voice Dream Reader makes it
so easy to bring text to speech.


97
00:04:03,944 --> 00:04:05,312
[electronic speaker]
Mr. Bennet was so odd.


98
00:04:05,345 --> 00:04:07,481
A mixture of quick parts,
sarcastic humor,


99
00:04:07,514 --> 00:04:09,149
reserve, and caprice...


100
00:04:09,183 --> 00:04:11,718
[Lauren] It has probably one
of the best implementations


101
00:04:11,752 --> 00:04:13,887
of voiceover
that we have ever seen.


102
00:04:13,921 --> 00:04:16,623
It has a lot
of text customization settings,


103
00:04:16.657 --> 00:04:19.626 line:-2
so it can increase contrast
or decrease contrast,


104
00:04:19.660 --> 00:04:24.164 line:-2
space out lines, words,
and highlight certain phrases


105
00:04:24.198 --> 00:04:26.266 line:-2
within a written material
to make it easy for people


106
00:04:26.300 --> 00:04:28.969 line:-2
who may have low vision
or dyslexia,


107
00:04:29.002 --> 00:04:32.105 line:-2
and it's also localized
into 26 different languages.


108
00:04:33.373 --> 00:04:36.410 line:-2
[Linda] This year's winner
in Inclusivity in games


109
00:04:36.443 --> 00:04:38.946 line:-1
is "HoloVista."


110
00:04:40,781 --> 00:04:43,884
"HoloVista"
is a mixed reality game


111
00:04:43,917 --> 00:04:46,587
where you use the gyroscope
to photograph


112
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:49,423
these really beautiful
3D spaces.


113
00:04:49.456 --> 00:04:52.125 line:-2
"HoloVista" has
a pretty thorough set


114
00:04:52.159 --> 00:04:54.428 line:-2
of accessibility controls
that make it


115
00:04:54.461 --> 00:04:57.231 line:-2
so that you can control
text legibility,


116
00:04:57.264 --> 00:05:00.334 line:-2
color legibility,
motion sensitivity,


117
00:05:00.367 --> 00:05:03.170 line:-2
and the way that you want
to control the camera


118
00:05:03.203 --> 00:05:04.905 line:-2
as you're panning around
or not.


119
00:05:04.938 --> 00:05:09.543 line:-2
[Teo] This app has got some
really great visual warnings


120
00:05:09.576 --> 00:05:13.013 line:-2
about potential sensory
and cognitive needs.


121
00:05:13.046 --> 00:05:16.049 line:-2
[Linda] It's also very good
at presenting those controls


122
00:05:16.083 --> 00:05:18.318 line:-1
and those warnings upfront.


123
00:05:18.352 --> 00:05:21.355 line:-1
♪ ♪


124
00:05:21.388 --> 00:05:23.957 line:-2
It's easy to know
what it feels like


125
00:05:23.991 --> 00:05:26.159 line:-2
to be delighted
and to have fun.


126
00:05:26,193 --> 00:05:30,030
Putting it into words
is a lot more difficult.


127
00:05:30,063 --> 00:05:31,198
[chuckles]


128
00:05:31,231 --> 00:05:33,100
[Alan] It's an interesting one
because you can feel delight


129
00:05:33,133 --> 00:05:36,236
having an experience
with a more serious app or game,


130
00:05:36,270 --> 00:05:38,105
or you can have delight and fun


131
00:05:38,138 --> 00:05:40,941
with, obviously, a game
